𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐏𝐫𝐨𝐛𝐥𝐞𝐦:
Startups and remote teams often struggle with secure internal network access. Relying on open ports or no encryption leads to major vulnerabilities:
•	Security Risks: Exposing internal servers (RDP, SSH, SMB) directly to the public internet invites brute-force attacks.
•	Data Sniffing: Remote employees using public Wi-Fi (cafes, airports) expose sensitive company data to intercept attacks.
•	Complex Client Setup: Many VPN protocols require complex, paid third-party client software, increasing IT support tickets.

𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐒𝐨𝐥𝐮𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧:
Deploying a native L2TP/IPSec VPN directly on the MikroTik edge router solves these infrastructure challenges efficiently:
•	Built-In Compatibility: L2TP/IPSec is natively supported by Windows, macOS, iOS, and Android. No client software installation is required.
•	Bank-Grade Encryption: IPSec provides robust AES-256 bit encryption, securing all traffic from the remote device to the office.
•	Centralized Network Control: Remote workers receive a local IP address, allowing strict firewall control over what resources they can access.

